  "description": "The (2,5) Cinquefoil torus knot has the highest pqScale of the common torus families at 0.976 — near-maximum coupling asymmetry. Five-petaled winding geometry creates beating patterns at non-octave, non-fifth intervals: the five-fold symmetry produces emergent harmonics that fall between the standard chromatic grid. macroKnot=0.65 blends deep into Solomon ring architecture — the five-petaled winding passes through the two-ring linked structure. LFO on braid depth at 0.03 Hz crosses WEAVE-I on each breath (33-second cycle). When the threshold is crossed, the five-fold structure crystallizes briefly into the knot.",
